# Git commits – no Cursor branding

When creating or amending git commits in this project:

- **Never** append "Made-with: Cursor" or any Cursor branding to commit messages.
- Use only the user-requested or conventional commit message (e.g. "Update README: ..."); do not add trailers, footers, or tags that mention Cursor or the IDE.
